{"word":"στέγη","slug":"στέγη","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>στέγη</b></el> <el>(στέγη, ἡ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:στέγω'><el>στέγω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a roof</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>tectum</el>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>a roofed place, a chamber, room</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>ἑρκεῖος στ.</el>, of <i>a tent</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <el>ἐκ κατώρυχος στέγη</el>, of the grave, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>often in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a>, like <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>tecta, a house, dwelling</el>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; <el>κατὰ στέγας</el> <i>at home</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}